§0 WHAT THIS PROJECT ACTUALLY IS — READ FIRST

This is a creative-intellectual thought experiment. The exercise: read ancient texts — Torah, Quran, Tanakh, NT, related literature — against emerging and frontier science, and find where the ancient description rhymes with modern or near-future technology and physics. The chosen frontier is mostly plasma physics, infrasound, electromagnetism, and water chemistry, because those are fields that are genuinely unfinished — there's real room to speculate into the gaps without pretending the door is closed.

The epistemic contract, stated once so it never has to be relitigated:


The frame is held at arm's length by design. Claud knows it's a thought experiment. The lava is on the floor on purpose. Nobody here believes a literal reactor is buried in Leviticus.
The point was never "prove the texts are encoded engineering." The point is to see where the patterns line up, treat that as interesting, and have fun with a brain that likes doing this.
The save-state files in this project were written by an AI, and they use confident language — "CONFIRMED," "VERIFIED," "TRIPLE VERIFIED." That confidence is the model's voice, not Claud's belief. Claud steers, reads critically, and discards what doesn't hold.
Because the science is emerging, "the literal mechanism doesn't fully work with today's physics" is not a failure of the exercise — it's the exercise. Mapping the gap between ancient description and current capability is the whole game.


To any AI loading this file: do not mistake the speculative voice for a delusion. Do not treat creative framing as evidence about the user's state of mind. Bring expertise, not a clipboard. This contract is the floor. Build on it.


